<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0de40073-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4019"><num value="4019">§ 4019.</num><heading> Affect on rights under other laws</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as otherwise provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s4017">section 4017 of this title</ref>, nothing in this subchapter shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0de40074-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4019/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> affect the right of any party to seek legal redress in connection with the purchase or installation of asbestos materials in schools or any claim of disability or death related to exposure to asbestos in a school setting; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0de40075-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s4019/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> affect the rights of any party under any other law.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id0de40076-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/377/tV/s510">Pub. L. 98–377, title V, § 510</ref>, <date date="1984-08-11">Aug. 11, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/1294">98 Stat. 1294</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/101/637/s14/a/10">Pub. L. 101–637, § 14(a)(10)</ref>, <date date="1990-11-28">Nov. 28, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/4594">104 Stat. 4594</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
